        public java.lang.String getCustomerEmail()
        If provided, this value will be used when the Customer object is created. If not provided, customers will be asked to enter their email address. Use this parameter to prefill customer data if you already have an email on file. To access information about the customer once a session is complete, use the customer attribute.

        public java.lang.String getLocale()
        The IETF language tag of the locale Checkout is displayed in. If blank or auto, the browser's locale is used.

        One of auto, bg, cs, da, de, el, en, en-GB, es, es-419, et, fi, fr, fr-CA, hu, id, it, ja, lt, lv, ms, mt, nb, nl, pl, pt, pt-BR, ro, ru, sk, sl, sv, tr, or zh.
